CRIMEAN-CONGO HEM. FEVER - RUSSIA (STAVROPOL) (02)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Crimean-Congo hem. fever - Russia (Stavropol) 20000513021247
Date: Tue, 16 May 2000 19:32:08 -0400
From: Alex Vladyko <vladyko@ns.briem.ac.by>
Source: ITAR-TASS news agency, 13 May 2000 [edited

A state of emergency has been declared in the Stavropol area in connection
with cases of Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever. It was announced by
Alexander Chernogorov, a governmental official of [the Stavropol area
(gubernator) [during the extraordinary Stavropol governmental session.
Gennady Onishchenko, a Chief Sanitary Physician and the Deputy of the
Health Minister of Russia, was presented at the session. In [the
Stavropol area 14 people have become ill, two of whom have died. Last year
11 people were ill with C-CHF and three of them died. The Stavropol area
center on the state san-epi surveillance informed that hemorrhagic fever
outbreaks were registered two years running, but there had been no reported
cases of hemorrhagic fever in the Stavropol area for 27 years. At the
session it was [noted that the fight against a disease vector, ticks,
should be supported additionally from the federal financial resources in
order to treat a natural foci of ticks with chemicals.
